<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-cjLaHjQGqNK0cLYBEW93Bg" name="test_motivator,_ueUMoHFfEdy8Ac588DXPCQ" guid="-cjLaHjQGqNK0cLYBEW93Bg" changeDate="2008-10-14T11:19:08.250-0700" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A test motivator is usually an external file that provides details about a test plan or test case. For example, a test&#xD;
    motivator file could be a document or spreadsheet containing detailed information about a specific test plan or test&#xD;
    case. It is convenient to be able to reference a test motivator file from a test plan and test case record. Test&#xD;
    motivators are useful in linking test requirements with test plans and test cases.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;div class=&quot;p&quot;>&#xD;
    You can use associations between test plan and test case records with a test motivator to determine: &#xD;
    &lt;ul>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            If there is test coverage for the motivator&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            If a test plan associated with a motivator has an associated external file&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;/div></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To provide focus for the test effort.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To enable the communication between the main stakeholders.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This information needs to be captured in a standalone or associated artifact. If not present then you might have to&#xD;
    deal with:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Lack&amp;nbsp;of focus for the test effort associated with a test cycle or iteration.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Lack of traceability support between the test main drivers and the test scope.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Communication problems between stakeholders, as the test coverage could not be properly checked.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This is a key artifact, but some organizations might capture this information within the test plan or even as part of&#xD;
    the associated test cases.&#xD;
&lt;/p></reasonsForNotNeeding>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
